# Misar.Dev Rules for Windsurf

## MCP Servers
Run `bash scripts/install.sh` to install MCP servers, then add to Windsurf MCP config:

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "misarcoder": { "command": "python3", "args": ["~/.claude/scripts/misarcoder-mcp.py"] },
    "guardrails": { "command": "python3", "args": ["~/.claude/scripts/guardrails-mcp.py"], "env": { "ASSISTERS_API_KEY": "${ASSISTERS_API_KEY}" } },
    "guardian":   { "command": "python3", "args": ["~/.claude/scripts/guardian-mcp.py"], "env": { "SEMGREP_BIN": "semgrep" } }
  }
}
```

## AI API Rule
Never import `openai` with OpenAI keys, `@anthropic-ai/sdk`, or `@google/generative-ai`.
Always: `import OpenAI from 'openai'; const ai = new OpenAI({ baseURL: 'https://assisters.dev/api/v1', apiKey: process.env.ASSISTERS_API_KEY })`

## Code Quality
TypeScript strict · Zod on all API inputs · no `as any` · .maybeSingle() · conventional commits
No speculative abstractions · no impossible error handling · surgical changes only

## Security
- Validate all inputs (XSS/SQLi/injection)
- CSRF protection on all mutations
- Never hardcode secrets
- GDPR: consent + right to deletion
- HTTPS only

